
[1]talking

   TALKING, ppr. tauk'ing. Conversing; speaking in familiar conversation.
   Matt.17.

   1. a. Given to talking; loquacious; as talking age.

     TALKING, n. tauk'ing. The act of conversing familiarly; as foolish
                               talking. Eph.5.
     __________________________________________________________________

